title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
so i've received a liquid damaged 820-00840-a in today. Liquid damage was focussed around the U7650 area. I've cleaned it all and visibly inspected the area - resoldered U7650 as pins 31 and 26 were not shiny anymore. 
If I connect charger it negotiates to 20v as expected but with a tiny spike to 0.07a current draw then drops to 0.00a. PPBUS is present at 13V but there is no PP5V_S5. PP5V_S5 is not shorted to ground either. I'm wondering if this is a dead U7650 or if water damage at U7650 might've killed U7800.

U7800 area is clean

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
First check diode mode to ground at 5V_S5.

Post basic voltages for U7650; pins 23, 12, 13, 22, 29, 21, 4.

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
diode mode reading is 0.455 to ground on pp5v_s5
pin 23 -13.06v
pin 12 - 0v
pin 13 - 0v
pin 22 - 3.3v
pin 29 - 0v
pin 21 - 0v
pin 4 - 0v

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message: Check U7800 (7 OF 10) LDO outputs at page 60.

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
PMIC_EN_P3V3S5 is missing?
What about PMIC_SHUTDOWN_L?

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
PMIC_EN_P3V3S5 is missing 0v
PMIC_SHUTDOWN_L at R7828 is 3.17v.

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message: R7828/29, which one is present on the board?

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message: R7828 is the one present, R7829 is not

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
Check if SMC_PM_G2_EN goes high.
If not, you may need to reball/replace SMC.
Also check signals and voltages at U5000 (SYM 2 OF 2) at page 39.

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
SMC_PM_G2_EN is high 3.4V
BUF_SMC_RESET_L is high 3.4v
PP1V2_S5_SMC_VDD - 1.2v
PP3V3_S5_SMC_VDD - 3.4v

also of note but probably not important right now L6600 and L6601 are missing. They appear to be just for audio so i'm not too concerned about them right now!

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
Looks like PMIC issue.
Be sure R7883 is good.

Do you get 3V1_RTC?

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message: 3v1_RTC is 0.023V so i'd say not there! PMIC issue then?

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message: Well i've pulled the PMIC and i've still got a 5ohm short to ground on 3v1_RTC. PCH i'm guessing?

title: 820-00840-a Wont start missing PP5V_S5
message:
A small chance to be one of C7922, or C1227/8.
Very likely bad PCH...
